1. How to leave a child in the ghetto?
Generally speaking, abandoned children want to put their children in a good family, so it makes sense to arrange the plot to secretly put the children in a car.
However, the car was stolen by a thief, who put the child in the ghetto, it is also reasonable.
A good screenwriter is one who puts two things together and never creates the story he or she needs.2. How to get your child adopted by a homeless person?
As a rule, a homeless person would not adopt a child if he could not live on his own. It is neither real nor interesting to let a homeless person take a child away.
A. the tramp sees A child near A trash can;
B. Remind the residents on both sides of the house whether they have lost their children out of kindness;
C, see someone pushing the cradle past, holding the child in the past, found not;
D. was about to put the child back, was targeted by the police;
E. trick a lame man into holding a child and then running away;
F. the lame man could not catch up, so he had to put the child in the cradle;
G, the owner of the cradle found the child, at the same time, found the tramp again, catch up;
H, the police again appeared, the homeless man speechless;
I, ready to throw the child into the sewer, saw the mother's message;
This design, let the story not only ups and downs, but also seems reasonable, the scriptwriter's wise view of this.3. How to design the livelihood of homeless people and children?
According to common sense, two people depend on each other, living a simple but peaceful life, but so designed, not only very plain, but also very conventional, the design of the play is: two people do bad things together, one is responsible for breaking glass, one is responsible for repairing glass; (the writers are so observant of life.) but it's not such a bad thing; Only when doing bad things can reflect the human wit and funny place;
How to enhance the visibility of this design? What if the police find out that the gang is doing something wrong? It's when the tramp pretends not to know the kid, and the kid doesn't understand what's going on.
